= Biogeochemical Cycles

== Hydrogen (Hydro/Water) Cycle

The surface water that comprises of the oceans the lakes of the earth
evaporates using the heat from the sun's radiation. This is called
_insolation_. Plants can also release water into the atmosphere by a
process called _transpiration_.

The formation of clouds is called _condensation_. Clouds are the clumped up
water in saturated liquid form. In the _cumolonimbus_ clouds, the clump becomes
tall and internal precipitation within the clouds happen. In contrast the
_cirrus_ clouds are those horizontal strips of clouds that signifies that the
weather is calm. _Transportation_ is the movement of clouds by wind.

